races.long_description: Raise and designate state funds for the Texas Technical College system.
Prohibit the state from enacting a tax on realized or unrealized capital gains.

Require judges to deny bail to individuals accused of certain violent or sexual felony offenses, provided the court finds that the accused is a danger to others or is unlikely to willingly return to court.

title.default: Proposition 4: Use Sales Tax for Water Fund

races.long_description: Establish a property tax exemption on animal feed held by the property owner for retail sale.

title.default: Proposition 6: Prohibit Taxes on Securities Transactions

races.ballot_measure_text: Proposition 6: Prohibit Taxes on Securities Transactions

races.ballot_measure_text: Proposition 7: Tax Exemption for Certain Surviving Spouses of Veterans

races.long_description: Prohibit the state from imposing estate taxes, as well as new taxes on estate transfers, inheritances and gifts.

races.seat: 9 - Tax Exemption for Personal Property Used for Income

races.seat: 10 - Tax Exemption for Homestead Fire Damage

races.ballot_measure_text: Proposition 10: Tax Exemption for Fire Damage

races.seat: 11 - Increase Property Tax Exemption for Elderly and Disabled

title.default: Proposition 11: Increase Property Tax Exemption for the Elderly and Disabled

races.ballot_measure_text: Proposition 11: Increase Property Tax Exemption for the Elderly and Disabled

races.long_description: Use $3 million from the states general fund to establish the Dementia Prevention and Research Institute of Texas.

Amend the state Constitution to bar persons who are not citizens of the United States from voting in Texas elections.

text.paragraph: In 2024, 87 percent of votes were reported by midnight on election night, and 96 percent were reported by noon the next day. A small share of voters cast ballots by mail, which must be postmarked by Election Day and arrive within three days.

In 2024, 91 percent of votes were reported by midnight on election night, and 96 percent were reported by noon the next day. Mail ballots must be postmarked by Election Day and received within six days.

Most voters cast votes by mail, and ballots can take days  or even weeks  to count. In 2024, about 49 percent of votes were reported by midnight Eastern time on election night, and 62 percent were reported by noon Eastern time the next day.
In the New York City Democratic mayoral primary in June, more than a third of votes were reported almost immediately after polls closed, and 93 percent of votes were reported by midnight.
In 2024, 83 percent of votes were reported by midnight on election night, and 97 were reported by noon the next day. Mail ballots must arrive by Election Day.

The contest features three leading candidates: Assemblyman Zohran Mamdani, a Democrat; former Gov. Andrew Cuomo, a Democrat running as an independent; and Curtis Sliwa, a Republican. Mr. Mamdani, a charismatic progressive would be the citys first Muslim mayor, and the youngest in a century. Mr. Cuomo is seeking a comeback after resigning from state office in 2021. See the latest polls.

Democrats are hoping to keep their 5-2 majority on the Pennsylvania state supreme court, with three justices who ran as Democrats up for re-election through retention. If they lose, Gov. Josh Shapiro will appoint replacements, to be confirmed by the Republican-controlled senate, which could lead to deadlock on the court.

The measure is an attempt by Democrats to counteract Republican gerrymanders President Trump has sought in red states. If approved, it would change Californias congressional district boundaries to make it easier for Democrats to flip five seats now held by Republicans.

Minneapolis voters will decide whether to give Mayor Jacob Frey a third term or to elect a challenger from the left flank of the Democratic Party, State Senator Omar Fateh. 

Mr. Frey, a relatively moderate Democrat, led Minneapolis during the riots that followed the murder of George Floyd in 2020 and fought against efforts to disband the citys Police Department. Mr. Fateh, a Democratic Socialist, would be the first Somali American to lead Minneapolis.

President Trump has loomed over the race for New Jersey governor. The Republican, Jack Ciattarelli, has run for the seat twice before, but this time he has the presidents endorsement. The Democrat, Representative Mikie Sherrill, has made opposition to Mr. Trump a focus of her campaign. See the latest polls.

Former Gov. Jim McGreevey of New Jersey left office in 2004 amid a sex scandal. He is seeking political rebirth as mayor of Jersey City in a field of locally prominent candidates. If no one receives more than 50 percent of the vote, there will be a runoff.

Abigail Spanberger, a Democrat and former Virginia congresswoman, has for months been favored over her Republican opponent, Winsome Earle-Sears, the current lieutenant governor. But a texting scandal involving the Democratic candidate for attorney general has added a degree of unpredictability in the races final weeks. See the latest polls.

Jay Jones, a Democrat and former Virginia state delegate, had been widely expected to defeat Jason Miyares, the incumbent attorney general and Trump-endorsed Republican nominee. But the discovery of violent texts sent by Mr. Jones in 2022 tightened the race considerably. See the latest polls.

Detroit voters will choose between Mary Sheffield, the City Council president, and Solomon Kinloch Jr., the pastor of a large church, as they select their first new mayor in 12 years. Both candidates are Democrats. Ms. Sheffield, who would be the first woman to lead Detroit, finished in first place by a large margin in the August primary. Mayor Mike Duggan, who guided Detroit out of bankruptcy, has endorsed Ms. Sheffield. He is running for governor of Michigan in 2026 instead of seeking a fourth term in City Hall.

Alvin Bragg, the Democratic incumbent, secured a high-profile conviction against Donald Trump in 2024. Mr. Bragg is favored to win against both the Republican candidate, Maud Maron, and Diana Florence, an independent.

The special election in a historically Black district features a new generation of rising Texas Democrats, including the Harris County attorney, Christian Menefee; State Representative Jolanda Jones; and a former Houston City Council member, Amanda Edwards. With a crowded field, a runoff is likely.

Minnesota voters will select new state senators to fill two vacant seats. Democrats currently hold a one-seat majority in the chamber. District 47, which leans Democratic, became vacant when Senator Nicole Mitchell, a Democrat, resigned after a burglary conviction. District 29, which leans Republican, became vacant when Senator Bruce Anderson, a Republican, died.

paragraphs.hed: Whats powering our forecast right now?
paragraphs.paragraph: Our live forecast makes use of three indicators in creating an estimate of the final result.
At the start of the night, our estimate is based on pre-election polls, past election results and demographic data.
As votes come in, we compare actual results to our pre-election estimates to create a statistical model of the remaining vote.
As a county reports more votes, these tabulated results will gradually supersede our previous estimates.

Virginia provides data for how voters are casting ballots, which our election model uses to estimate the nature of the votes that remain to be counted. These estimates are also based on polling, historical voting data and the votes reported so far.

text.paragraph: Note: Voting method data may not include all reported votes as ballots are still being tallied. Provisional ballots are reported after Election Day and are not included above. In the 2024 presidential election, provisional ballots made up around 2 percent of all votes in Virginia.
In 2024, these ballots were fairly representative of the final vote.
